news.title: Resolve all pending land partition cases in two months: Mohali ADC
news.para: ADC Tidke said, "It came to my notice that there has been a yearlong backlog of various cases pertaining to revenue department. Directions have been issued to the revenue officers to dispose of all such pending files within two months."

news.title: Rajasthan govt launches e-auction to set up 31 M-sand manufacturing units
news.para: According to the auction timeline, interested parties can submit bids on the Government of India's e-portal between Jan 28 and Feb 6.

news.title: Geberit reports flat 2024 sales but expects construction industry to stabilise
news.para: The maker of toilets, bathroom ceramics and piping said its sales met the previous year's level with 3.085 billion Swiss francs ($3.38 billion), in a difficult construction market as higher interest rates and economic uncertainty weighed on building projects.

news.title: Home sales in Canada drop 5.8% in December 2024
news.para: The fourth quarter increase stood among the stronger quarters for activity in the last 20 years outside of the pandemic, CREA said.

news.title: Hawaii lawmakers vow to stabilize property insurance market
news.para: Hurricanes in Florida and North Carolina and wildfires in California affect the insurance business in Hawaii because insurance companies buy reinsurance - insurance for themselves - on the global market.

news.title: GuocoLand secures two green loans totalling $908 million
news.para: The deals comprised a S$1.14 billion green loan, GuocoLand's largest to date, for the refinancing of its latest mixed property development, Guoco Midtown, and another for S$105 million to refinance its Midtown Bay luxury residential development, the company said.

news.title: Gurugram civic body orders removal of C&D waste from roadside
news.para: The dumping was not only a threat to the environment and health of the residents of the area, but also an eye sore, Prasad said.

news.title: Aligarh civic body issues notice to AMU over Rs 24.4 crore tax dues
news.para: Officials at AMC said that the dues pertain to 40 properties owned by the university. Tax payments for 22 properties had been cleared earlier, leaving Rs 24.4 crore unpaid for 18 properties, the officials added.

news.title: Tax dues of Karads’ flat paid online after Pimpri Chinchwad civic body's warning
news.para: Earlier in the evening, Avinash Shinde, assistant municipal commissioner and head of PCMC's property tax department, told TOI, "The owners have not paid property tax since June 2021.

news.title: Bhubaneswar civic body introduces chatbot to property tax payments
news.para: In partnership with a private bank, BMC introduced a WhatsApp chatbot that allows residents to pay property taxes, trade licence fees and access various municipal services through their smartphones.

news.title: Nashik civic body streamlines process for building plan approval
news.para: The executive engineer (EE) will have the power to give permission for building plan proposals for projects on land measuring 301 to 4,000 sqmt.

news.title: Kanpur development body intensifies efforts for New Kanpur City project
news.para: It is presently preparing the site plan based on acquired land and its topography to ascertain precise land locations and requisite infrastructure development. The infrastructure work encompasses roads, sewerage systems and drinking water pipelines.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh CM announces to form civic body in Vidisha
news.para: CM Yadav also said that several other demands of the region would also be fulfilled and Vidisha would achieve a new height in terms of development.

news.title: Spain is considering a 100% tax on homes bought by foreigners
news.para: Spanish Prime Minister Pedro Sanchez announced the plan this week to tackle housing affordability and high rents in the Southern European nation. He said that the overall goal was to provide "more housing, better regulation and greater aid."

news.title: Sundaram Alternates raises over Rs 1,000 crore for SA RE Credit Fund IV
news.para: The SA RE Credit Fund IV will focus primarily on South Indian micro markets with established developers. The fund is 70% deployed in a portfolio that is yielding close to 19% IRRs.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government plans to revive scheme to regularize encroached house sites
news.para: Sources said that chief minister Chandrababu Naidu has decided to regularize house-sites of the poor who encroached govt lands.

news.title: J&K CM urges officers to adopt urban-planning strategies for planned development
news.para: Abdullah was speaking at a meeting convened here to review and discuss the implementation of proposed urban-planning schemes and policies aimed at transforming the Union Territory's urban landscape to bring about planned development.

news.title: Special drive in South Goa to act against illegal constructions
news.para: The initiative aims to streamline the disposal of cases by bringing together applicants and key department representatives under one roof.

news.title: Every poor person in the country will have a permanent house: Madhya Pradesh CM
news.para: Referring to an old survey in Madhya Pradesh, he said that permanent houses are to be provided to 16 lakh beneficiaries and the state has got 8.5 lakh new houses as of now.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Builder fined for illegally trimming seven trees in Chandkheda
news.para: A video that went viral showed the top branches of seven trees being cut at Zanzar Sky construction site in Chandkheda on Jan 12, prompting a team from the Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation to visit the site the next day.
